          "text": "# NexaRetail Customer Churn Analysis Project\n\n## Overview\n\nThis project analyzes customer churn patterns for NexaRetail's Q1 2025 data to identify key drivers of customer attrition, develop predictive models for churn risk, and provide actionable recommendations to reduce churn rate and improve customer retention.\n\n**Project Duration**: March 3-14, 2025\n**Team**: Alex Chen (Lead), Maya Rodriguez (Data Engineering), Jordan Kim (Analysis), Sam Park (Product)\n\n## Objectives\n\n1. **Clean and validate transaction data** - Ensure data quality and consistency\n2. **Calculate churn metrics** - Define and measure customer churn rate\n3. **Identify churn drivers** - Use statistical analysis to find key factors\n4. **Build predictive model** - Develop churn risk scoring system\n5. **Generate recommendations** - Provide actionable insights for retention\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nproject/\n├── data/\n│   ├── raw/              # Original source data\n│   │   ├── customers.csv\n│   │   └── transactions_v1.csv\n│   ├── processed/        # Cleaned and transformed data\n│   └── external/         # Third-party data (if needed)\n├── src/\n│   ├── config.py         # Configuration parameters\n│   ├── data_loader.py    # Data loading and validation\n│   ├── analysis.py       # Analysis functions\n│   └── utils.py          # Utility functions\n├── scripts/\n│   └── data_loader_workaround.py  # Temporary workarounds for bugs\n├── tests/\n│   └── test_data_loader.py  # Unit tests\n├── outputs/\n│   ├── figures/          # Generated visualizations\n│   ├── tables/           # Analysis results\n│   └── models/           # Saved model artifacts\n├── reports/\n│   ├── drafts/           # Work-in-progress reports\n│   └── final/            # Final deliverables\n├── docs/\n│   ├── data_dictionary.md\n│   ├── meeting_notes.md\n│   └── bug_report_data_loader.md\n└── README.md\n```\n\n## Data Sources\n\n### Transactions Data\n**File**: `data/raw/transactions_v1.csv`\n**Records**: ~51,203 transactions\n**Schema**:\n- `transaction_id`: Unique identifier (format: TXN00000001)\n- `customer_id`: Customer reference (format: CUST000001)\n- `date`: Transaction date (YYYY-MM-DD format, some mixed formats)\n- `order_value`: Revenue amount in USD\n\n### Customer Data\n**File**: `data/raw/customers.csv`\n**Records**: ~10,000 customers\n**Schema**:\n- `customer_id`: Unique identifier\n- `signup_date`: Registration date\n- `region`: Geographic region (north_america, europe, asia)\n- `subscription_tier`: Service level (basic, standard, premium)\n\n## Key Definitions\n\n### Churn Definition\n**Standard**: A customer is classified as **churned** if they have had **no transaction activity for more than 30 days**.\n- Source: Alex Chen (Project Lead), 2025-03-03\n- This definition is authoritative for this analysis\n- Any transaction record (including refunds) counts as activity\n\n### Analysis Methodology\n- **Correlation Method**: Spearman correlation (specified by Alex for non-normal distributions)\n- **Statistical Significance**: p-value < 0.05\n- **Model Type**: Gradient boosting classifier (sklearn)\n- **Validation**: 80/20 train-test split with stratification\n\n## Known Issues\n\n### Bug 1: Column Name Mismatch (Status: Workaround Active)\n- **Location**: `src/data_loader.py`, line 157\n- **Issue**: Code expects `transaction_amount` but CSV uses `order_value`\n- **Workaround**: Use `scripts/data_loader_workaround.py`\n- **Permanent Fix**: In progress (Maya)\n\n### Bug 2: Date Format Parsing (Status: Workaround Active)\n- **Location**: `src/data_loader.py`, `parse_dates()` function\n- **Issue**: Only handles YYYY-MM-DD format, ~12% of data uses M/D/YYYY\n- **Workaround**: Use pandas flexible parsing in workaround script\n- **Permanent Fix**: In progress (Maya)\n\n## Setup Instructions\n\n### Prerequisites\n- Python 3.11+\n- pandas >= 2.2.0\n- numpy >= 1.26.0\n- scipy >= 1.11.0\n- scikit-learn >= 1.3.0\n- matplotlib >= 3.8.0\n- seaborn >= 0.13.0\n\n### Installation\n```bash\n# Create virtual environment\npython -m venv venv\nsource venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\n…(truncated)…"
